title: Connect to Device over WiFi
description: Connects to a device over WiFi instead of USB. You'll need to know the device's IP address, and it must be on the same network as your computer.

androidVersions.notes: Requires developer options enabled and ADB debugging turned on

title: Get Current Activity (Foreground App)
description: Shows the current activity that's in the foreground. Useful for debugging or automation to determine what's currently visible on screen.

versions.notes: Android 12 introduced activity recents command for current activity

31.output: * Recent #0: Task{41450e7 #8 type=home I=com.google.android.apps.nexuslauncher/.NexusLauncherActivity U=0 rootTaskId=1 visible=true mode=fullscreen translucent=false sz=1}

versions.windows: adb shell dumpsys activity activities | grep mResumedActivity
versions.mac: adb shell dumpsys activity activities | grep mResumedActivity
versions.notes: Android 14 changed format, use mResumedActivity for current foreground activity

title: Check Package Info
description: Gets detailed information about a specific package (app), including version, install time, and permissions.

androidVersions.notes: Core ADB command that works across all Android versions

androidVersions.notes: Efficient single-command process using exec-out

title: Install APK
description: Installs an APK file onto the connected device. Add the '-r' flag to replace an existing application.

androidVersions.notes: Core ADB command that works across all Android versions

title: Install APK to Specific User
description: Installs an APK for a specific user on a multi-user device. Particularly useful in enterprise environments with work profiles.

androidVersions.notes: Requires multi-user support for installing to specific users
